raw_data.title: Business Analyst I
raw_data.description:
Analyzes financial and non-financial transactions, processes, policies, and procedures to identify trends and performance metrics for program results and measurements.
Conducts transactional and data analysis to identify current state analysis, gap analysis, benchmarking, best practices identification, organizational assessment, and other related analysis to forecast outcomes. 
Coordinates with business and technology stakeholders and teams to ascertain system requirements, such as program/accounting functions, output requirements, input data acquisition, and system techniques and controls. 
Plans and implements process improvements, including future state design, change management, and transition planning. Conduct client interviews. 
May deliver presentations and training courses including measurement, analysis, improvement, and program control. 
May perform cost and benefit analysis and other special studies to improve financial and non-financial (e.g., accounting operations).

Lead negotiation responsibilities.

raw_data.title: Information Technology Support
raw_data.description:
Responsibilities:
Performs all duties associated with being the assistant to the Lead System Administrator for IT Systems. Provides technical support for configuration, installation, problem isolation, and problem resolution. Possess computer skills to perform work in DOS and past and current Microsoft Operating Systems. Must be able to troubleshoot, evaluate and diagnose problems from File Servers to Network electronics to PC workstations and printers.  Must have basic knowledge of computers and information systems processes. Must be able to apply both rational and creative processes and approaches to identify root causes of problems and their solutions.  Must convey information clearly and effectively through formal and informal documents/communication.  Must possess interpersonal skills and work well with all levels of management, associates, and users.  Requires a working knowledge of Systems or Domain Administration to include creating, deleting and customizing users’ accounts, queues, workgroups and stations, troubleshooting and resolving problems using the relevant software; managing and maintaining servers and subsystems, ensuring minimal down time. Ability to install off-the-shelf and customized software.  Provide technical support to include monitoring government servers, switches, and routers for alerts; Identify and troubleshoot issues and problems before they adversely affect end- users; Maintain servers and services; Maintain server security logs.  Create, delete and unlock domains, email accounts, virtual private networks (VPN), dial-up and Blackberry accounts following specified procedures; Set up group accounts, distribution lists, and public folders and grant permissions to end-users; Add computers and printers to the domains and grant proper permissions to users; Create home drives and set quota limits; Set mailbox storage space; Use Active Directory and DRA to create, delete, unlock and reset accounts, and grant permissions to mailboxes and group accounts; shall have a secret security clearance at time of contract award; will assist on SIPRNet system maintenance.
Provide second and third level help desk support. This includes but is not limited to providing assistance with Microsoft Outlook and web access including creating and deleting users’ profiles and troubleshooting various email problems; Assist end-users and IT POCs troubleshooting ticket issues.
